See: http://vimcasts.org/episodes/synchronizing-plugins-with-git-submodules-and-pathogen/

For vim-airline, use one of these modified fonts: https://github.com/Lokaltog/powerline-fonts
Currently, i use SourceCodePro.

Installing your Vim environment on another machine:
cd ~
git clone http://github.com/marcbey/vimfiles.git ~/.vim
ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
cd ~/.vim
git submodule init
git submodule update

Upgrading a plugin bundle:
cd ~/.vim/bundle/fugitive
git pull origin master

Upgrading all bundled plugins: 
git submodule foreach git pull origin master

Add a plugin (eg. vinegar):
cd ~/.vim
git submodule add http://github.com/tpope/vim-vinegar.git bundle/vinegar
git add .
git commit -m "Install Fugitive.vim bundle as a submodule."


Remove a submodule (dont forget to remove traces also in vimrc):
cd ~/.vim
git submodule deinit bundle/nerdtree
git rm bundle/nerdtree
git commit -m "Remove nerdtree plugin"
